    <header>
      <h1>Library Management System</h1>
    </header>
    <section>
      <p>
        The Library Management System is a software application that helps in maintaining the records of the books available in the library, the users who have taken those books, and the staff managing the library. The system automates all the manual processes involved in managing a library.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Book catalog management</li>
        <li>Users information management</li>
        <li>Automatic book issue and return management</li>
        <li>Fine calculation for late book returns</li>
        <li>Generation of reports for books and users</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Benefits</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Reduces manual work and saves time</li>
        <li>Accurate and up-to-date information about books and users</li>
        <li>Improves the overall efficiency of the library</li>
        <li>Eliminates the chances of errors in manual record-keeping</li>
        <li>Provides easy access to information for library staff and users</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
